    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# üí≥ Workflow 4: Automated Invoice Generation via Airtable + PDFMonkey  \n\n## üõ†Ô∏è How the Invoice Trigger Works  \n\n## üöÄ Invoice Process  \n1. **Webhook Node**  \n   - Airtable checks the **Project Percentage** field.  \n   - If `= 100%` ‚Üí **Generate Invoice button** is available.  \n   - When pressed, Airtable sends the project data to n8n via a **Webhook**.  \n   - Captures important project fields (Client name, Email, Project ID, Price, etc.).  \n\n2. **PDFMonkey - Create Invoice**  \n   - Use an **HTTP POST** request to PDFMonkey.  \n   - Send captured data from Airtable.  \n   - Include a variable `status: pending` to indicate invoice creation.  \n\n3. **PDFMonkey - Retrieve Invoice PDF**  \n   - Use an **HTTP GET** request with the document ID from the POST step.  \n   - Retrieve invoice file links:  \n     - üì• Downloadable PDF URL  \n     - üåê Public share link  \n\n4. **Merge + Flatten**  \n   - Merge the invoice URLs with Airtable record data.  \n   - Flatten into a single array for clean mapping.  \n\n5. **Email Client**  \n   - Use **Gmail Node** to send the invoice PDF as an attachment.  \n   - Subject: ‚ÄúYour Project Invoice from [Company]‚Äù  \n   - Body: includes public invoice link + payment instructions.  \n\n6. **Slack Notification**  \n   - From the same flattened data, send a Slack message to the client‚Äôs private channel:  \n     - ‚Äú‚úÖ Your project is now **100% complete**. An invoice has been generated and sent to your email.‚Äù  ",
        "height": 880,
        "width": 2288
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -720,
        1088
      ],
